CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1773162679
OL,3,CParents in Surrey are being urged not
OL,4,Cto buy smartphones for their children
OL,6,FThe letter says that phones leave
OL,7,Fyoung people more exposed to harmful
OL,8,Fcontent, often unintentionally. This
OL,9,Fincludes pornography, cyberbullying
OL,10,Fand extremist ideology.
OL,12,FIt also notes an increased risk of
OL,13,Fanxiety and low moods in young people,
OL,14,Fespecially those who started using a
OL,15,Fmobile phone earlier.
OL,17,FSurrey schools say there is little
OL,18,Fevidence of owning a phone adding any
OL,19,F"true value" to pupils lives.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
